							<h2>How to Install and Setup</h2>
							<p>
								The <a href="http://cookbook.liftweb.net/">Lift Cookbook</a>
								is the most up-to-date resource to learn how to use Lift.
								First off, you should learn how to
								<a href="http://cookbook.liftweb.net/#DownloadAndRun">Download and Run</a> Lift.
								Then, if you use an IDE, you can learn how to use them with Lift:
								you can set up <a href="http://cookbook.liftweb.net/#idea">IntelliJ IDEA</a> or
								<a href="http://cookbook.liftweb.net/#eclipse">Eclipse</a>.
							</p>

							<h2>From an MVC background</h2>
							<p>
								If you're coming from an MVC background (like Rails, Struts,
								etc.), there's a
								<a
									href="http://simply.liftweb.net/index-Chapter-13.html#toc-Chapter-13">Chapter for you</a>
								.
								The code examples are included and you can run them yourself.
							</p>

